{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:01:38.496Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Curse of Dimensionality"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the phenomenon where "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "data becomes extremely sparse and algorithms fail"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as the number of features (dimensions) grows — the volume of the feature space increases so rapidly that available data can't fill it, making it exponentially harder to find meaningful patterns, clusters, or neighbors."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The curse occurs when classifying, organizing, and analyzing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "high-dimensional data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that doesn't occur in low-dimensional spaces:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"As the number of features or dimensions grows, the amount of data we need to generalize accurately grows exponentially.\""}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Core problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- As dimensionality increases, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "volume of space drastically increases"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Data becomes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "more and more sparse"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (spread out)\n- Algorithms need "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "way more data to generalize"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Intuition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Imagine finding a coin dropped on:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "1D line"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Walk the line, find it easily\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "2D field (100×100 m)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Hard — football ground to search\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "3D space (100×100×100 m)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Nearly impossible — 30-story building to search"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "As dimensions increase, the search becomes exponentially harder."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It Happens: Data Sparsity"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "The Geometry"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Consider a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "unit square"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (2D) with a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "circle inscribed"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2D Square with Circle:\n┌──────────┐\n│    ●     │  ← Most points in circle\n│  ●   ●   │  ← Sparse points on corners\n│    ●     │\n└──────────┘"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Most points lie within the circle"}, {"type": "text", "text": "; sparse data on corners."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adding Dimensions"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "3D"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Unit cube with inscribed sphere:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Volume of cube = 1\nVolume of sphere = π/6 ≈ 0.52\n\nMore points are on corners than before!"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Higher dimensions"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (n-dimensional):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Volume of hypercube = 1 (always)\nVolume of hypersphere (n-ball) = decreases exponentially\n\nAs n → ∞:\n- Volume of sphere → 0\n- More points lie on corners!"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Always more and more points lie on the corners as dimensions increase."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Problems"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Curse of Dimensionality — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data Sparsity"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Volume growth"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Space volume grows exponentially with dimensions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data fills less"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Given data fills less and less of the data space"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exponential data needed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Amount of data needed grows exponentially with dimensionality"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Statistical significance"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sparsity breaks statistical methods that require significance"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 15 features (yes/no questions) → need "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "2¹⁵ ≈ 32,000 training samples"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule of thumb"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": At least "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "5 training examples per dimension"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Distance Concentration"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Distance metrics (especially Euclidean) "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "lose relevance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as dimensions increase:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Euclidean distance formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$d = \\sqrt{\\sum"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{i=1}^{d} (x_i - y_i)^2}$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "d"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of dimensions"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": As you add dimensions:\n- Sum increases → distance becomes larger\n- Ratio between nearest and farthest point "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "approaches 1"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- All points become "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "approximately equidistant"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- \"K nearest points\" concept becomes meaningless\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "KNN fails"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Can't identify nearest neighbors\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K-means fails"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Can't form meaningful clusters (all observations equally alike/different)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "LOF (Local Outlier Factor) fails"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Nearest neighbor search meaningless"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model Performance Degradation"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regression"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decreasing performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Classification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decreasing performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Clustering"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decreasing performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Common patterns"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Internal/boundary patterns from low-dim become invalid"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cause"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Data distribution and heterogeneity become complex and counterintuitive."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Redundant Features"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Issue"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Consequence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Highly correlated features"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Add noise, not information"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-correlated features"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dilute signal-to-noise ratio"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Redundant features"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Skew PCA variance contribution to few dimensions"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-World Example: Fruit Classification"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Goal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Identify fruit perfectly"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Features:\n- Color (1 feature)\n- Weight (1 feature)\n- Shape (1 feature)\n- Texture (1 feature)\n- ... (15 total yes/no features)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- 15 features × 2 values each = 2¹⁵ ≈ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "32,000 training samples needed"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Infinite features → infinite training samples → "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "no real-world usefulness"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Smaller training set → use fewer features."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When Does It Start?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Even 10 dimensions"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (seems low) can bring on the curse"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Typical scenarios"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Images (pixels = features)\n- Text (words = features)\n- Genomics (genes = features)\n- Tabular data with many columns"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solutions to Combat the Curse"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Technique"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Works"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Remove correlated features"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Eliminate redundancy, keep only important ones"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Group similar features"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Combine related features into single representation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Project to lower dimensions, keep most variance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "LDA (Linear Discriminant Analysis)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Supervised dimensionality reduction"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "t-SNE"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Non-linear dimensionality reduction for visualization"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "UMAP"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Modern non-linear reduction method"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature selection"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pick subset of most relevant original features"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Dimensionality Reduction Works"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PCA approach"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Find directions of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "maximum variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Project data onto fewer dimensions\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Preserve most information"}, {"type": "text", "text": " while reducing sparsity"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Faster training\n- Less overfitting\n- Improved visualization\n- Better algorithm performance"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Curse of Dimensionality"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Data sparsity + algorithm failure in high-dimensional spaces"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Core problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Volume grows exponentially → data becomes sparse → need exponentially more data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": 5 training examples per dimension minimum"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Distance concentration"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": All points become equidistant → nearest neighbor search meaningless"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Algorithms fail"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": KNN, K-means, LOF break down"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model degradation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Regression, classification, clustering performance drops"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Redundant features"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Correlated features add noise, skew PCA variance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Starts at 10 dimensions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Even modest dimensionality triggers the curse"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Dimensionality reduction (PCA, t-SNE, UMAP, feature selection)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Deep learning exception"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Neural networks can overcome the curse through learned representations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Curse of Dimensionality is the \"search-in-an-empty-building\" problem — as dimensions increase, the feature space explodes so fast that data becomes impossibly sparse, making distances meaningless and algorithms fail, so dimensionality reduction (PCA, t-SNE, feature selection) is essential to compress high-dimensional data while preserving structure."}]}]}}